TC1: Verify product search with a valid keyword (Positive)
Steps:
Navigate to the homepage
Enter a valid keyword (e.g., “Shoes”) in the search bar
Click search
Expected Result:
Relevant products related to “Shoes” should be displayed

TC2: Validate search with invalid keyword (Negative)
Steps:
Enter random keyword (e.g., “123abc”)
Click search
Expected Result:
No products should be displayed
An appropriate message, like “No results found” should appear

TC3: Verify search with empty input (Edge Case)
Steps:
Leave the search field empty
Click search
Expected Result:
The system should either: Show all products OR
Display validation message (no crash should occur)
Add to Cart

TC4: Verify adding product to cart successfully (Positive)
Steps:
Search for a product
Select a product
Click “Add to Cart”
Expected Result:
The product should be added to the cart
The cart count should increase

TC5: Validate adding out-of-stock product to cart (Negative)
Steps:
Open a product marked as “Sold Out”
Try to click “Add to Cart”
Expected Result:
Add to Cart button should be disabled OR
The product should not be added to the cart

TC6: Verify adding product without selecting required options (Edge Case)
Steps:
Open a product with variants (e.g., size)
Do not select any option
Click “Add to Cart”
Expected Result:
The system should prompt the user to select the required options
The product should not be added to the cart
